The paper discusses a library for synthesizing FPGA designs in a modular and abstract way using standard programming language features such as types and higher-order functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with hardware description languages and high-level synthesis, which are topics that fall under the Architecture (cs.AR) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also mentions FPGA computations, which are relevant to the Embedded Systems (cs.ET) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of an image processing library, which falls under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
